==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Phycomycetes
<hw>Phy`co*my*ce"tes</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.;
Gr. <grk>fy^kos</grk> seaweed + <ets>mycetes</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A large, important class of parasitic or
saprophytic fungi, the algal or algalike fungi. The plant body ranges
from an undifferentiated mass of protoplasm to a well-developed and
much-branched mycelium. Reproduction is mainly sexual, by the formation
of conidia or sporangia; but the group shows every form of transition
from this method through simple conjugation to perfect sexual
reproduction by egg and sperm in the higher forms.</def> --
<wordforms><wf>Phy`co*my*ce"tous</wf> <pr>(#)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Phycophaeine</ent>⟦br⟧
